messages.message: Hi, a friend of mine working at a real estate investment firm spends considerable time looking at annual reports (as the one he sent me attached) and then re-inserts portions of the data into excel and slides. I had him try Converse and he'd like to be able to download the retrieved data directly into Excel (as Build allows) for financial modelling. Is this on the roadmap? cc @Varun Jain @Lee
You can already download retreived tables to excel. Is this what they're looking for?
@avi it's not letting me download it at all when the table is long and when I can it's only in Csv or txt output
